⁣KFC- Korean fried cauliflower made with an instant tempura batter from @oki.singapore. I try not to deep fry at home so this felt like such a treat. The sauce is the same base I used for the Korean fried chicken I made in Italy! I don't like my savory foods to be sweet so I omit the sugar they usually goes into the sauce ⠀
⠀
Ingredients:⠀
1 Head of cauliflower, cut into bite sized pieces, ⠀
2 tablespoons of rice flour⠀
100g of Oki Tempura batter mix⠀
OKI Canola oil⠀
130g of cold water ⠀
1 tablespoon of Sesame oil⠀
1 tablespoon garlic, grated⠀
3 tablespoons of ketchup⠀
2.5 tablespoons of Gochujang⠀
1 tablespoon of Soy sauce⠀
1 tablespoon of Korean rice syrup or Honey⠀
Spring onions and sesame seeds as needed⠀
⠀
🥣 Method:⠀
1. Mix the Oki tempura batter mix with the cold water, mix to combine but do not overwork the batter⠀
⠀
2. Dip the cauliflower dusted with rice flour into the batter, then into a pot with OKI canola oil heated to 180C. Fry for 6-7 minutes until deep golden brown. Reserve on paper towels⠀
⠀
3. To make the sauce. In a wok, add the sesame oil and grated garlic, saute it till the raw taste of the garlic is removed. Spray in a bit of sake as an optional step, add all the rest of the ingredients and heat till just starting to bubble. Add in the reserved fried cauliflower and toss to combine. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seeds and spring onions.
